You are given an array of products with categories:

javascript
const products = [
  { name: "Laptop", category: "Electronics" },
  { name: "Shirt", category: "Clothing" },
  { name: "Mouse", category: "Electronics" },
  { name: "Jeans", category: "Clothing" },
  { name: "Phone", category: "Electronics" }
];
Task:
Write a function getUniqueCategories(products) that returns an object containing:

categories: an array of unique category names (preserving first occurrence order)

firstCategory: the first unique category

total: number of unique categories

Use for...of, Set, and destructuring. Do not modify the original array.

Expected output:

js
{
  categories: ["Electronics", "Clothing"],
  firstCategory: "Electronics",
  total: 2
}
